{"questionId":"21314","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Deb used a thermometer to record the maximum daily temperature over ten consecutive days.&nbsp;Her results, in degrees Celsius (<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>°</mo><mtext>C</mtext></math>), are shown below.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>14</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>15</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>14</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>11</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>10</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>9</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>14</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>15</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>16</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>13</mn></math></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\">For this data set, find the value of</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>the mean.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mn>14</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>15</mn><mo>+</mo><mo>…</mo></mrow><mn>10</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>13</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>1</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"21314","referenceCode":"21M.1.SL.TZ1.2b","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"the mean.","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 4—Statistics and probability","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","SL 4.3—Mean, median, mode. Mean of grouped data, standard deviation. Quartiles, IQR"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}